In [28]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(ncols=2, nrows=1, figsize = (20,9))

#First Graph - Bar Graph

ax[0].set_title("Distribution of Type", fontdict={"size": 18})
figure = sns.countplot(x=data.Type, ax=ax[0], order=["L", "M", "H"])
for container in figure.containers:
    figure.bar_label(container)
ax[0].set_ylabel("Frequency", fontdict={"size": 15})

#Second Graph - Pie Graph

ax[1].set_title("Distribution of Type - Pie", fontdict={"size":18})
ax[1].pie(x=data.Type.value_counts().values, labels=data.Type.value_counts().index, autopct='%1.2f%%', explode=[0, 0, 0.3])

plt.show()

plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
numerical_columns = data.select_dtypes(include=["float", "int"]).columns

for i, col in enumerate(numerical_columns, 1):
    plt.subplot(2, 3, i)
    sns.histplot(data[col], kde=True )
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {col}')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

fig, ax = plt.subplots(ncols=2 , nrows= 1, figsize= (23,12))

#First figure - Bar Graph

ax[0].set_title("Target Type - Bar", fontdict={"size": 18})
figure = sns.countplot(x=data["Target"], ax=ax[0] ,order=data["Target"].value_counts().index)
for container in figure.containers:
    figure.bar_label(container)
ax[0].set_ylabel("Frequency", fontdict={"size": 15})

#Second Figure - Pie Graph

ax[1].set_title("Target Type - Pie", fontdict={"size":18})
ax[1].pie(x=data["Target"].value_counts().values, labels = data["Target"].value_counts().index, autopct ='%1.2f%%',
          explode=[.3, 0.2])

plt.show()

#Failure By type pairplot

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

plt.figure(figsize=(30, 25))
pairplot = sns.pairplot(data=data, hue="Failure Type")
pairplot.fig.suptitle('Failure by Type', fontsize=24)
pairplot.fig.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)  
plt.show()
